---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="What to Wear for a Passport Photo: The Ultimate Guide 2026"
  description="Learn exactly what to wear for a passport photo. Discover the best colors, what to avoid, and rules for glasses, uniforms, and headwear for a perfect photo."
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 mt-[80px] md:mt-10 mb-20">
    <nav class="mb-8" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <li><a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a></li>
        <li><span class="text-gray-400">/</span></li>
        <li><a href="/passport" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Passport</a></li>
        <li><span class="text-gray-400">/</span></li>
        <li class="text-gray-900">What to Wear</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="font-crimson text-[40px] md:text-[50px] leading-tight text-gray-900 mb-6">
      What to Wear for a Passport Photo: Official Guidelines
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700">
      <p>
        Getting your passport photo taken can be stressful. The last thing you want is for your application to be rejected because of a wardrobe malfunction. If you're wondering <strong>what to wear for a passport photo</strong>, you are not alone. 
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-3xl mt-10 mb-4 text-gray-900">1. The Best Colors to Wear</h2>
      <p>
        Always wear a color that contrasts with the background. Since most countries (including the US and UK) require a white or off-white background, you should avoid wearing a white shirt. 
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Recommended:</strong> Dark colors like navy, black, dark green, or deep red.</li>
        <li><strong>Avoid:</strong> White, cream, or very light pastels that might blend into the background.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-3xl mt-10 mb-4 text-gray-900">2. Everyday Clothing vs. Uniforms</h2>
      <p>
        You must wear everyday attire. Uniforms, clothing that looks like a uniform, and camouflage attire are strictly prohibited and will result in an immediate rejection of your photo.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-crimson text-3xl mt-10 mb-4 text-gray-900">3. Glasses and Headwear</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Glasses:</strong> You cannot wear glasses in your passport photo. You must take them off, even if you wear them daily.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Headwear:</strong> Hats and head coverings are generally not allowed. The only exception is for religious or medical purposes, and you must provide a signed statement verifying this. Even then, the head covering cannot obscure your hairline or cast shadows on your face.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 bg-blue-50 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center">
        <h3 class="font-crimson text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-4">Ready to take your photo?</h3>
        <p class="mb-6">Use our free passport photo maker to get the exact dimensions you need for your country.</p>
        <a href="/passport" class="inline-block bg-primary text-white font-bold px-8 py-3 rounded-full hover:bg-primary-dark transition-colors">
          Create Passport Photo
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
